      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting, but that sounds a bit contradictory. you mentioned disincentives from the tax system but also that it led to an increase in participation. wouldn't the \"disincentive to work\" argument be more significant for people who might choose to stay home if they get enough support? i've seen a lot of reports saying these programs actually discourage people from looking for jobs.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
